AESTDY Study Day of Start of Adverse Event integer Timing $3.
Derived
logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }
AEENDY Study Day of End of Adverse Event integer Timing $3.
Derived
logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }
AEDUR Duration of Adverse Event integer Timing $2.
Derived
All duration calculations are calculated as: duration = ymd(enddate) - ymd(startdate)

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }
CMENDY Study Day of End of Medication integer Timing $3.
Derived

logr::put("ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED") ds <- data.frame(ds) %>% dplyr::mutate_all(., as.character) %>% ## Derive DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD variables ## The unite function is used to combine YEAR-MM-DD to derive --DTC variables ## The function lubridate:ymd(x) ensures the format is ISO8601 dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) %>% # Disposition Event Date tidyr::unite(., col = 'DSDTC', 'DS_YY', 'DS_MM', 'DS_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Oncologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'ONNOTDTC', 'ONNOT_YY', 'ONNOT_MM', 'ONNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Ophthalmologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTDTC', 'OPNOT_YY', 'OPNOT_MM', 'OPNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTSCDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTASDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # End of Double-masked Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVDTC', 'V3INV_Y', 'V3INV_M', 'V3INV_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Informed of Open-Label dplyr::mutate(., V3INV2DTC = V3INVDTC) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVSCDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVASDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5OL_Y', 'V5OL_M', 'V5OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 5 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVSCDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 5 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVASDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6OL_Y', 'V6OL_M', 'V6OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVSCDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVASDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7_YY', 'V7_MM', 'V7_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVSCDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVASDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) ds[apply(ds, 2, str_detect, "9999")] <- NA

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

QSDY Study Day of Finding integer Timing $3.

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

Assigned based on VISITNUM & SVENDTC & EOP: logr::put("## MAPS SEENDTC TO THE NEXT VISIT -1 DAY OR END OF PARTICIPATION") di_seendtc <- function(x) { ## Capture end of participation date if available xx <- db %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'SE.SEENDTC', "DS_YY", "DS_MM", "DS_DD", sep = '-', remove = FALSE) %>% dplyr::select(., USUBJID, SE.SEENDTC) ## Replace missing dates with NA xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$SE.SEENDTC == "NA-NA-NA"] <- NA ## Replace missing dates with NA x$SESTDTC[x$SESTDTC == "NA-NA-NA"] <- NA ## Define the end of participation date eop <- xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$USUBJID %in% x$USUBJID[1]] ## Assign an index for the first missing date (NA) in SESTDTC indx <- which(is.na(x$SESTDTC))[1] ## Apply an end of participation date if applicable to the last SESTDTC x$SESTDTC[indx] <- eop ## Define the end of the SESTDTC period by the next SESTDTC - 1 day x$SEENDTC <- dplyr::lead(ymd(x$SESTDTC), n = 1, default = NA) -1 ## If subject has no EOP date, end the function if (is.na(eop)) { xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx } else ## Define the EOP as the last element and return the dates x$SEENDTC[indx] <- eop # x$SEENDTC[length(x$SESTDTC)] <- x$SESTDTC[length(x$SESTDTC)] xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx } logr::put("## CALCULATE START STUDY DAYS FOR DATASET") sestdy <- c() for (i in 1:length(se$USUBJID)) { sestdy[i] <- di_dy_trial(usubjid = se$USUBJID[i], dtc = se$SESTDTC[i]) print(i) } se$SESTDY[] <- unlist(as.character(sestdy))

logr::put("## ADD VISITNUM FROM SDTM DICTIONARY") logr::put("## MAPS VARIABLE LABELS BASED ON SDTM_METADATA DICTIONARY") di_map_visitnum <- function(x) { # Determine unique Variable Name and index to Field Label indx <- which(sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` %in% x) visitnum = base::unique(sdtm_dictionary$VISITNUM[indx]) # If the variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # and returns character(0) sets conditions for next if(length(indx) < 1) { visitnum = -1 } # If the variable is in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` but # no sdtm_dictionary$`Field label` sets conditions for next if(is.na(visitnum)) { visitnum = -1 } # If variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # return blank if(!between(visitnum, 0, 364)) { return("NA") } else { # Map label to Field Label y <- sdtm_dictionary$VISITNUM[indx] return(as.character(y)) } } suppsv$IDVARVAL <- unlist(sapply(1:length(suppsv$QNAM), function(x) di_map_visitnum(suppsv$QNAM[x])))

logr::put("## MAPS VARIABLE CRF PAGE BASED ON SDTM_METADATA DICTIONARY") di_map_qorig <- function(x) { # Determine unique Variable Name and index to Field Label indx <- which(sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` %in% x) qorig = base::unique(sdtm_dictionary$CRFPG[indx]) # If the variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # and returns character(0) sets conditions for next if(length(indx) < 1) { qorig = -1 } # If the variable is in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` but # no sdtm_dictionary$`Field label` sets conditions for next if(is.na(qorig)) { qorig = -1 } # If variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # return blank if(qorig == -1) { return("") } else { # Map label to Field Label y <- sdtm_dictionary$CRFPG[indx] return(y) } } logr::put("## ADD CRF PAGE FROM SDTM DICTIONARY") suppsv$QORIG <- unlist(sapply(1:length(suppsv$QNAM), function(x) di_map_qorig(suppsv$QNAM[x])))

logr::put("## DERIVE DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD") sv <- sv %>% ## Derive DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD variables ## The unite function is used to combine YEAR-MM-DD to derive --DTC variables ## The function lubridate:ymd(x) ensures the format is ISO8601 # Site visit 1 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC1', 'V1_YY', 'V1_MM', 'V1_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 2 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC2', 'V2_YY', 'V2_MM', 'V2_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 3 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC3', 'V3_YY', 'V3_MM', 'V3_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 4 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC4', 'V4_YY', 'V4_MM', 'V4_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 5 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC5', 'V5_YY', 'V5_MM', 'V5_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 6 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC6', 'V6_YY', 'V6_MM', 'V6_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Site visit 7 tidyr::unite(., col = 'SVSTDTC7', 'V7_YY', 'V7_MM', 'V7_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE)
SVENDTC End Date/Time of Observation date Timing YYMMDD10. ISO 8601
Derived
All visit occur in a single setting, thus SVENDTC is derived from SVSTDTC; time data is not collected

Derived
logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }
SVENDY Study Day of End of Observation integer Timing $3.
Derived
logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

Methods

Methods
Method Type Description
AEDTC derivation Computation
Notes: The function di_map_options() maps variables to their options. This results in the mapping of month, day, and timing entries per the logical statments below: IF AEDTC_DD == 'UN' THEN AEDTC_DD == "01" IF AEDTC_MM == 'UNK' THEN AEDTC_MM == "01" CODE: ae <- ae %<% di_map_options(ae) ae %<% ##maps options tidyr::unite(., col = 'AEDCT', 'AEDCT_YY', 'AEDCT_MM', 'AEDCT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% ##derives DTC variable lubridate::ymd(AEDTC) ##ensures format of DTC variable is ISO8601
AESEQ derivation Computation
Unique sequence based on sort order of STUDYID USUBJID AEDECOD AESTDTC AEENDTC: ae <- ae %<% dplyr::group_by(., USUBJID) %>% dplyr::mutate(.,AESEQ = 1:length(USUBJID)) %>% di_ungroup_by("USUBJID") %>% data.frame()
AEENDTC derivation Computation
Notes: The function di_map_options() maps variables to their options. This results in the mapping of month, day, and timing entries per the logical statments below: IF AEENDTC_DD == 'UN' THEN AEENDTC_DD == "01" IF AEENDTC_MM == 'UNK' THEN AEENDTC_MM == "01" CODE: ae <- ae %<% di_map_options(ae) ae %<% ##maps options tidyr::unite(., col = 'AEENDCT', 'AEDCT_YY', 'AEENDCT_MM', 'AEENDCT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% ##derives DTC variable lubridate::ymd(AEENDTC) ##ensures format of DTC variable is ISO8601
EPOCH hardcode Computation
Hardcoded to dates between subject elements with di_epoch_trial()
AESTDTC derivation Computation
Notes: The function di_map_options() maps variables to their options. This results in the mapping of month, day, and timing entries per the logical statments below: IF AESTDTC_DD == 'UN' THEN AESTDTC_DD == "01" IF AESTDTC_MM == 'UNK' THEN AESTDTC_MM == "01" CODE: ae <- ae %<% di_map_options(ae) ae %<% ##maps options tidyr::unite(., col = 'AESTDCT', 'AESTDCT_YY', 'AESTDCT_MM', 'AESTDCT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% ##derives DTC variable lubridate::ymd(AESTDTC) ##ensures format of DTC variable is ISO8601

Set to null because no subject was randomized to an unplanned arm and no reason needed

Hardcoded to USA
DMDTC derivation Computation
Since subjects are consented and start study on the same visit, DMDTC is derived from RFICDTC
DTHDTC derivation Computation
IF AEOUT == "Death" THEN DTHDTC == AEDTC[AEOUT == "Death"] ELSE Null
DTHFL derivation Computation
IF AEOUT == "Death" THEN DTHFL='N' ELSE DTHFL='Y'
DM.INVID Other
RACE derivation Computation
dm$RACE.American_Indian_or_Alaska_Native <- ifelse(dm$RACE.American_Indian_or_Alaska_Native == "1", "American Indian or Alaska Native", "") dm$DM.RACE.Asian <- ifelse(dm$RACE.Asian == "1", "Asian", "") dm$RACE.Black_or_African_American <- ifelse(dm$RACE.Black_or_African_American == "1", "Black or African American", "") dm$RACE.Native_Hawaiian_or_Other_Pacific_Islander <- ifelse(dm$DM.RACE.Native_Hawaiian_or_Other_Pacific_Islander == "1", "Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander", "") dm$RACE.White <- ifelse(db$DM.RACE.White == "1", "White", "") dm <- dm %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'RACE', 'RACE.American_Indian_or_Alaska_Native', 'RACE.Asian', 'RACE.Black_or_African_American', 'RACE.Native_Hawaiian_or_Other_Pacific_Islander', 'RACE.White', sep = ' ', remove = TRUE) dm$RACE <- str_trim(dm$RACE, "both") dm$RACE <- ifelse(dm$RACE.Other == 1, dm$RACEOTH, dm$RACE)
RFENDTC derivation Computation
RFENDTC is the last date of dosing from the source dosing dataset
DM.RFICDTC Other
RFPENDTC derivation Computation
RFPENDTC is the end of particpation dat from derived DSDTC variable
RFSTDTC derivation Computation
Since subjects are consented and start study on the same visit, RFSTDTC is derived from RFICDTC
DM.RFXENDTC Other
RFXSTDTC derivation Computation
Since subjects are consented and start study on the same visit, RFXSTDTC is derived from RFICDTC + 1
DM.SITEID Other
DSCAT derivation Computation
All hardcode (for example): dplyr::mutate(., DSCAT = "Protocol Milestone")
DSDECOD derivation Computation
All hardcode (for example): dplyr::mutate(., DSDECOD = "ENDMASKED")
DSSEQ derivation Computation
logr::put("DERIVE --SEQ WITH DEFINED SDTM_METADATA$TOC_METADATA$DOMAINKEYS") ds <- ds %>% dplyr::group_by(., USUBJID) %>% dplyr::arrange(., USUBJID, DSSTDTC) %>% dplyr::mutate(.,DSSEQ = 1:length(USUBJID))
DSSTDTC derivation Computation
logr::put("ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED") ds <- data.frame(ds) %>% dplyr::mutate_all(., as.character) %>% ## Derive DTC, STDTC, and ENDTC from --DTC_YY, --DTC_MM, --DTC_DD variables ## The unite function is used to combine YEAR-MM-DD to derive --DTC variables ## The function lubridate:ymd(x) ensures the format is ISO8601 dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) %>% # Disposition Event Date tidyr::unite(., col = 'DSDTC', 'DS_YY', 'DS_MM', 'DS_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Oncologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'ONNOTDTC', 'ONNOT_YY', 'ONNOT_MM', 'ONNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Notification of Ophthalmologist tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTDTC', 'OPNOT_YY', 'OPNOT_MM', 'OPNOT_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTSCDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'OPNOTASDTC', 'OPNOTDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # End of Double-masked Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVDTC', 'V3INV_Y', 'V3INV_M', 'V3INV_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Informed of Open-Label dplyr::mutate(., V3INV2DTC = V3INVDTC) %>% # Visit 3 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVSCDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 3 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V3INVASDTC', 'V3INVDTC', 'V3SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5OL_Y', 'V5OL_M', 'V5OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 5 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVSCDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 5 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V5INVASDTC', 'V5OL3DTC', 'V5SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6OL_Y', 'V6OL_M', 'V6OL_D', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVSCDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V6INVASDTC', 'V6OL3DTC', 'V6SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Opt-in to Long Term Open Label Phase Continuation tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7_YY', 'V7_MM', 'V7_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% # Visit 6 Scleral Lens Removed tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVSCDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM1', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) %>% # Visit 6 Assessments Begin tidyr::unite(., col = 'V7INVASDTC', 'V7OL3DTC', 'V7SCRTM2', sep = ' ', remove = FALSE) ds[apply(ds, 2, str_detect, "9999")] <- NA
DSTERM derivation Computation
End of Particpation is from DSTERM in codelist; all others are hardcode to terms (for example): ds_v3mc <- ds %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = ds_cols_v3mc) %>% tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = "V3INVDTC", values_to = "DSSTDTC", names_to = "DSTERM") %>% dplyr::mutate(., DSTERM = ifelse(is.na(V3INV), "Double-masked Phase Not Completed", "Double-masked Phase Completed"))
EPOCH derivation Computation
All hardcode (for example): dplyr::mutate(., EPOCH = "Masked Phase") Alternatively, EOP is coded the following: logr::put("## SEARCH FOR EPOCH BASED ON DATES WITH di_epoch_trial FUNCTION") epoch <- c() for (i in 1:length(ds_eos$USUBJID)) { epoch[i] <- di_epoch_trial(usubjid = ds_eos$USUBJID[i], dtc = ds_eos$DSSTDTC[i]) print(i) } ds_eos$EPOCH <- epoch
DURATION derivation Computation
All duration calculations are calculated as: duration = ymd(enddate) - ymd(startdate)
DVENDTC derivation Computation
logr::put(""ADD ASSIGNED/HARDCODED VARIABLES AS REQUIRED"") dv <- data.frame(dv) %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'DVENDTC', 'DVEN_YY', 'DVEN_MM', 'DVEN_DD', sep = '-', remove = TRUE) %>% dplyr::mutate(., DVENDTC = lubridate::ymd(DVENDTC))
DVSEQ derivation Computation

logr::put("## MAPS VARIABLE OPTIONS BASED ON SDTM_METADATA CODELISTS") di_map_options <- function(x) { # Collect variable names from the dataset cols <- base::colnames(x) # Collect date variable names from the dataset cols_dtc <- cols[stringr::str_detect(base::colnames(x), "DTC_|OCMST(M|D|Y)|_(DD|MM|YY)")] # Collect non-date variable names from the dataset cols_var <- cols[-which(cols %in% cols_dtc)] # For loop to map nonb-date variable options from source variables for (i in base::which(cols %in% cols_var)) { # Determine unique CODELISTNAME (grouping name) indx <- which(sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` %in% cols[i]) gname = base::unique(sdtm_dictionary$`Optiongroup name`[indx]) # If the variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # and returns character(0) sets conditions for next if(length(indx) < 1) { gname = 1 } # If the variable is in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` but # no sdtm_dictionary$`Optiongroup name` sets conditions for next if(is.na(gname)) { gname = 1 } # If variable does not exist in sdtm_code$sourcevariable move to next variable if(gname == 1) { next } else { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% gname) %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,i] <- sapply(x[,i], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } } if(length(cols_dtc) < 1) { return(x) } else { # For loop to map variable date (DAY. MONTH) options from source variables for (ii in base::which(cols %in% cols_dtc)) { # Maps MONTH variables, DERIVES "01" if MONTH == UNK if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_MM|DTC_M|OCMSTM|_MM")) { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% "MONTH") %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,ii] <- sapply(x[,ii], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } # Maps DAY variables, DERIVES "01" if DAY == UN if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_DD|DTC_D|OCMSTD|_DD")) { # Filter the sdtm_code based on unique CODELISTNAME lookup <- base::data.frame(sdtm_code) %>% dplyr::filter(., CODELISTNAME %in% "DAY") %>% dplyr::select(., sourcevalue, CODEDVALUE) # Map map variable options from sourcevalue to CODEVALUE via lookup x[,ii] <- sapply(x[,ii], function(y) lookup$CODEDVALUE[match(y, lookup$sourcevalue)]) } # Ignores any mapping of YEAR variables if(stringr::str_detect(cols[ii], "DTC_YY|DTC_Y|OCMSTY|_YY")){ # x[,ii] <- base::sapply(x[,ii], # function(y) base::ifelse(base::is.na(x[,ii]), "9999", # base::unlist(x[,ii]))) } # Collect time variable names from the dataset cols_tm <- cols[stringr::str_detect(base::colnames(x), "TM|TIM|FSWO")] } } x }

SEENDTC derivation Computation
Assigned based on VISITNUM & SVENDTC & EOP: logr::put("## MAPS SEENDTC TO THE NEXT VISIT -1 DAY OR END OF PARTICIPATION") di_seendtc <- function(x) { ## Capture end of participation date if available xx <- db %>% tidyr::unite(., col = 'SE.SEENDTC', "DS_YY", "DS_MM", "DS_DD", sep = '-', remove = FALSE) %>% dplyr::select(., USUBJID, SE.SEENDTC) ## Replace missing dates with NA xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$SE.SEENDTC == "NA-NA-NA"] <- NA ## Replace missing dates with NA x$SESTDTC[x$SESTDTC == "NA-NA-NA"] <- NA ## Define the end of participation date eop <- xx$SE.SEENDTC[xx$USUBJID %in% x$USUBJID[1]] ## Assign an index for the first missing date (NA) in SESTDTC indx <- which(is.na(x$SESTDTC))[1] ## Apply an end of participation date if applicable to the last SESTDTC x$SESTDTC[indx] <- eop ## Define the end of the SESTDTC period by the next SESTDTC - 1 day x$SEENDTC <- dplyr::lead(ymd(x$SESTDTC), n = 1, default = NA) -1 ## If subject has no EOP date, end the function if (is.na(eop)) { xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx } else ## Define the EOP as the last element and return the dates x$SEENDTC[indx] <- eop # x$SEENDTC[length(x$SESTDTC)] <- x$SESTDTC[length(x$SESTDTC)] xxx <- x %>% dplyr::select(STUDYID, DOMAIN, USUBJID, SESEQ, ETCD, ELEMENT, TAETORD, EPOCH, SESTDTC, SEENDTC, SESTDY,SEENDY) xxx } logr::put("## CALCULATE START STUDY DAYS FOR DATASET") sestdy <- c() for (i in 1:length(se$USUBJID)) { sestdy[i] <- di_dy_trial(usubjid = se$USUBJID[i], dtc = se$SESTDTC[i]) print(i) } se$SESTDY[] <- unlist(as.character(sestdy))

--DY derivation Computation
logr::put("## STUDYDAYS FUNCTION TO CALCULATE THE STUDY DAY FROM USUBJID & REFSTDTC") di_dy_trial <- function(usubjid = "GL14-315", dtc = "2021-05-20") { # ensure dtc is a character dtc <- base::as.character(dtc) IsDate <- function(mydate) { # Check if field is a date using as.Date that looks for unambiguous dates # Assumes date format so NA returned not Character error. # Why? with no date format, R tries two defaults then gives error. # BUT With a dateformat R returns NA # Args # Suspected date and optional date format string # Returns # TRUE if thinbks it is a date tryCatch(!is.na(as.Date(mydate)), error = function(err) {FALSE}) } if(!IsDate(dtc)) { return(NA) } if(is.na(str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}"))) { return(NA) } else if (!str_detect(dtc, "^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}")|str_detect(dtc,"9999")) { return(NA) } else dtc <- str_extract(dtc, "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # evaluates dataset for defined start date (RFICDTC) in database x <- base::data.frame(db) %>% dplyr::filter(USUBJID %in% usubjid) %>% dplyr::select_at(., .vars = c("USUBJID", "ICFDTC")) %>% dplyr::mutate(., ICFDTC = dmy(ICFDTC)) icfdtc <- str_extract(as.character(x$ICFDTC), "[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}") # returns the difference in dates if (dtc < icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(icfdtc, dtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc > icfdtc) { dy = base::as.character(base::floor(base::difftime(dtc, icfdtc, units = c("days")))) } if (dtc == icfdtc) { dy = 0 } dy }

logr::put("## ADD VISITNUM FROM SDTM DICTIONARY") logr::put("## MAPS VARIABLE LABELS BASED ON SDTM_METADATA DICTIONARY") di_map_visitnum <- function(x) { # Determine unique Variable Name and index to Field Label indx <- which(sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` %in% x) visitnum = base::unique(sdtm_dictionary$VISITNUM[indx]) # If the variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # and returns character(0) sets conditions for next if(length(indx) < 1) { visitnum = -1 } # If the variable is in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` but # no sdtm_dictionary$`Field label` sets conditions for next if(is.na(visitnum)) { visitnum = -1 } # If variable does not exist in sdtm_dictionary$`Variable name` # return blank if(!between(visitnum, 0, 364)) { return("NA") } else { # Map label to Field Label y <- sdtm_dictionary$VISITNUM[indx] return(as.character(y)) } } suppsv$IDVARVAL <- unlist(sapply(1:length(suppsv$QNAM), function(x) di_map_visitnum(suppsv$QNAM[x])))
